title: World Classics in Literature (Tell Me Why #114)(gnv64)
description:
World Classics in Literature (Tell Me Why #114)
By Manorama
English | March 2016 | PDF | 194 pages | 11 mb
scanned to PDF by me.

Many children lie, and get punished. Very soon it is forgotten, too. Not so, the punishment Pinnochio got for lying. It is etched in the minds of children across the world. For each lie Pinnochio said his nose would grow longer. The story of Pinnochio, the naughty wooden puppet, never dies in our memory, as he is a
character immortalised in the classic novel written by Carlo Collodi.
There are many such stories, poems..and literary masterpieces that will live on in our minds, as long as human civilization lasts. These are the classics. There are many such classic works in literature, originating from different parts of the world and from various times in history.
This issue of Tell Me Why tells you about some of those important works in world literature.
